    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="610"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d610">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 E. W./12–2245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Finland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hulley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Helsinki</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-22">December 22,
                            1945</date>.<lb/>[Received December 23—10:11 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>795. Press 22d. After lengthy deliberation, war trial court<note n="70"
                        xml:id="d610fn1">The special war trial court was composed of 15 justices.
                        Three of these were judges from other Finnish courts, and the remaining 12
                        were members of the Finnish Diet who were chosen by the Diet on the basis of
                        proportional representation.</note> ordered seven accused imprisoned;
                    Kukkonen alone remaining at <pb facs="0636" n="624" xml:id="pg_624"/> liberty.
                    Eight justices voted for imprisoning Reinikka and Kivimaki as compared with four
                    [on] previous occasions. Ten voted for rearresting Tanner as compared with six
                    previously. Four voted for rearresting Kukkonen both times. Eleven voted for
                    keeping Ryti, Rangell, Ramsay and Linkomies in custody as compared with eight
                    previously.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Helsingen Sanomat</hi>
                    <note n="71" xml:id="d610fn2">A Helsinki daily newspaper affiliated with the
                        National Progressive Party.</note> comments “Court decision yesterday
                    calculated to soft-pedal Soviet criticism sent from here in reports on trial and
                    ease tension that surrounded question politically since end first phase of
                    trial. Easing of tension will be regarded as relief by responsible Finnish
                    authorities.”</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hulley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
